1
00:00:01,013 --> 00:00:02,546
(Previously)
I'm just a tourist who got lost.

2
00:00:03,200 --> 00:00:04,699
You wanted to help him...

3
00:00:04,700 --> 00:00:07,400
because you wanted to go down
to the city with him, didn't you?

4
00:00:07,800 --> 00:00:09,300
You must stay here!

5
00:00:11,000 --> 00:00:12,176
I just want to be your friend.

6
00:00:12,200 --> 00:00:13,599
Outsiders cannot be trusted.

7
00:00:13,600 --> 00:00:14,500
But I trust him.
Will you go to Bangkok with me?

8
00:00:15,501 --> 00:00:17,299
If you want to find your mother,
I will help you.

9
00:00:17,300 --> 00:00:18,300
Really?

10
00:00:20,000 --> 00:00:21,600
Fire! Fire!

11
00:00:22,500 --> 00:00:24,500
Welcome, Mr. Gaysorn.

12
00:00:50,000 --> 00:00:51,170
Let's go.

13
00:00:51,570 --> 00:00:52,570
Pruek, wait.

14
00:00:53,053 --> 00:00:54,680
Why do I have to run?

15
00:00:56,433 --> 00:00:57,710
Bussaba, listen to me.

16
00:00:58,893 --> 00:01:00,850
They know about your scent

17
00:01:01,167 --> 00:01:03,448
and they will go after you,
to make a perfume out of you.

18
00:01:04,040 --> 00:01:07,310
If I don't let them,
my scent will soon disappear.

19
00:01:07,720 --> 00:01:09,290
What are they going to do to me?

20
00:01:09,993 --> 00:01:12,747
They can do anything for money.

21
00:01:13,867 --> 00:01:15,136
You need to leave this place, fast.

22
00:01:15,160 --> 00:01:17,450
I'll find you
after I'm done handling things from here.

23
00:01:23,611 --> 00:01:24,612
Gaysorn, my baby.

24
00:01:26,133 --> 00:01:27,413
You need to leave with your mom,

25
00:01:27,800 --> 00:01:29,640
and I will see you later,
as fast as possible.

26
00:01:43,427 --> 00:01:45,428
[6 Months Later]

27
00:01:54,193 --> 00:01:55,194
Bussaba.

28
00:02:12,770 --> 00:02:14,490
Since the beginning of your pregnancy

29
00:02:14,773 --> 00:02:16,620
to now when you're about to give birth,

30
00:02:18,160 --> 00:02:19,850
I haven't seen your husband, not once.

31
00:02:22,573 --> 00:02:24,120
Are you sure

32
00:02:24,293 --> 00:02:25,930
that he won't leave you?

33
00:02:26,850 --> 00:02:28,547
Pruek won't leave or lie to me.

34
00:02:30,370 --> 00:02:32,393
He told us to run away

35
00:02:33,187 --> 00:02:34,810
because people are after us.

36
00:02:37,887 --> 00:02:39,010
Is it true

37
00:02:39,807 --> 00:02:42,250
that city people want your
scent to make a perfume?

38
00:02:46,960 --> 00:02:49,210
Pruek extracted the scent from my body.

39
00:02:51,770 --> 00:02:53,207
After they smelled my scent,

40
00:02:55,220 --> 00:02:56,820
they wanted to make a perfume out of it.

41
00:02:57,746 --> 00:02:59,626
They treated you like
you're not a human being.

42
00:03:01,727 --> 00:03:03,007
Such a horrible group of people.

43
00:03:05,813 --> 00:03:09,360
Did you tell him that

44
00:03:10,580 --> 00:03:12,310
Mudan women

45
00:03:13,007 --> 00:03:14,310
will lose their scent

46
00:03:15,473 --> 00:03:17,547
after they give birth?

47
00:04:37,000 --> 00:04:40,500
"Flower Boy"
(Episode 3)

48
00:04:45,570 --> 00:04:46,850
You should rest here first.

49
00:04:52,713 --> 00:04:53,833
I'll turn the TV on for you.

50
00:04:55,093 --> 00:04:58,250
You can select the channels with this.

51
00:05:00,533 --> 00:05:01,813
I'll get you something to drink.

52
00:05:10,127 --> 00:05:11,210
Oh my!

53
00:05:11,800 --> 00:05:13,101
Hey!

54
00:05:16,853 --> 00:05:19,010
That's too loud. It
could upset the neighbor.

55
00:05:20,153 --> 00:05:21,770
Who is your neighbor?

56
00:05:23,713 --> 00:05:26,330
I don't know him, he's an old foreigner.

57
00:05:26,980 --> 00:05:28,900
I don't know his name,
I've never talked to him.

58
00:05:29,360 --> 00:05:30,361
What do you mean?

59
00:05:31,920 --> 00:05:33,520
You're neighbors but you don't know him?

60
00:05:35,027 --> 00:05:36,730
We live independently.

61
00:05:38,000 --> 00:05:39,360
I go out to work in the morning.

62
00:05:39,947 --> 00:05:42,427
After work, I go home and
I don't normally see my neighbors.

63
00:05:44,960 --> 00:05:47,493
It's getting late,
I think you should go to bed.

64
00:05:47,953 --> 00:05:49,513
I'll get you something to eat tomorrow.

65
00:05:54,373 --> 00:05:55,373
Wait, stop.

66
00:05:56,827 --> 00:05:58,107
We traveled all day to get here.

67
00:05:59,147 --> 00:06:00,387
You should take a shower first.

68
00:06:03,927 --> 00:06:04,928
Follow me.

69
00:06:06,667 --> 00:06:07,890
This is your bathroom.

70
00:06:13,140 --> 00:06:16,050
You can adjust hot and cold water here.

71
00:06:17,947 --> 00:06:18,948
Really?

72
00:06:24,447 --> 00:06:26,073
- What?
- Hey! Relax.

73
00:06:27,450 --> 00:06:30,250
Calm down, it's just water.

74
00:06:39,813 --> 00:06:40,814
It's too cold.

75
00:06:43,920 --> 00:06:45,360
You can adjust it to be warmer here.

76
00:08:07,747 --> 00:08:08,747
Here's your towel.

77
00:08:13,933 --> 00:08:16,080
I think you should just take a shower.

78
00:08:23,733 --> 00:08:24,734
- Right!
- Hey!

79
00:08:29,907 --> 00:08:32,690
I was going to say that
you can leave your wet clothes here.

80
00:08:33,073 --> 00:08:34,593
I'll get someone to wash them for you.

81
00:08:50,133 --> 00:08:51,843
I will go to the city and look for Gaysorn.

82
00:08:51,867 --> 00:08:53,170
What is your plan?

83
00:08:54,720 --> 00:08:57,050
The furthest you've been is the market.

84
00:08:57,667 --> 00:09:00,380
And nobody among us
has ever been to Bangkok.

85
00:09:01,700 --> 00:09:04,570
Bussaba told me that Bangkok was huge.

86
00:09:04,820 --> 00:09:06,020
How are you going to find him?

87
00:09:06,880 --> 00:09:09,133
We can't let him run away like that.

88
00:09:12,533 --> 00:09:15,450
Gaysorn said that he
would be gone for one month.

89
00:09:17,553 --> 00:09:19,410
And he is a man of his word.

90
00:09:20,787 --> 00:09:22,367
We should wait a little bit longer,

91
00:09:23,247 --> 00:09:24,248
just one month.

92
00:09:29,727 --> 00:09:30,850
Gaysorn will come back

93
00:09:32,500 --> 00:09:33,571
by the next full moon.

94
00:10:19,947 --> 00:10:21,490
Hello, Scent?

95
00:10:22,250 --> 00:10:25,370
Sun, do you know why
Mudan people are so fragrant?

96
00:10:26,153 --> 00:10:29,113
I have no idea and I really
want to ask Gaysorn about that.

97
00:10:29,420 --> 00:10:30,770
Wait, did you learn something?

98
00:10:31,800 --> 00:10:32,960
I want to tell you something.

99
00:10:35,527 --> 00:10:36,727
I don't know how to explain it

100
00:10:38,847 --> 00:10:41,994
but Gaysorn hasn't always
been fragrant all the time.

101
00:10:43,060 --> 00:10:45,530
His scent comes and goes.

102
00:10:47,073 --> 00:10:48,074
It's normal.

103
00:10:48,533 --> 00:10:51,250
Scientifically speaking,
people's scent is unstable.

104
00:10:51,760 --> 00:10:52,930
What do you mean by that?

105
00:10:55,320 --> 00:10:56,650
Listen to me carefully, buddy.

106
00:10:57,440 --> 00:11:00,947
People's scent varies and
is based on many factors like

107
00:11:01,347 --> 00:11:04,210
our body temperature, sweat, stress

108
00:11:04,700 --> 00:11:06,087
or our hormones.

109
00:11:06,633 --> 00:11:08,993
The point is that I have no idea

110
00:11:09,187 --> 00:11:11,130
what can stimulate the
scent of the Mudan people.

111
00:11:14,940 --> 00:11:16,913
How can we make perfume out of them?

112
00:12:46,560 --> 00:12:47,561
What are you doing?

113
00:12:55,927 --> 00:12:57,287
I'm dropping off some clothes for you.

114
00:13:59,927 --> 00:14:02,033
Here's your food.

115
00:14:07,140 --> 00:14:08,141
Mata,

116
00:14:09,133 --> 00:14:11,613
I think I will ask city people around
about Gaysorn this time.

117
00:14:12,453 --> 00:14:13,840
What is your plan?

118
00:14:14,620 --> 00:14:17,210
Just asking people if they saw Gaysorn

119
00:14:17,410 --> 00:14:18,693
with that guy named Scent.

120
00:14:20,173 --> 00:14:22,293
- Someone could've seen them.
- No need.

121
00:14:25,227 --> 00:14:27,340
It's like finding a needle in a haystack.

122
00:14:30,667 --> 00:14:31,747
We can do nothing but wait.

123
00:14:53,507 --> 00:14:54,508
Morning.

124
00:14:55,740 --> 00:14:56,741
How are you?

125
00:14:57,853 --> 00:14:59,854
Do I have to wear these?

126
00:15:02,147 --> 00:15:03,187
Why? It looks cute on you.

127
00:15:04,220 --> 00:15:07,410
A little too big, I guess.
We will find you new clothes today.

128
00:15:08,507 --> 00:15:10,370
Can't I wear my own clothes?

129
00:15:11,353 --> 00:15:13,060
But this is how we dress.

130
00:15:13,660 --> 00:15:15,767
You need to dress like this to blend in.

131
00:15:17,953 --> 00:15:18,970
Let's eat.

132
00:15:19,533 --> 00:15:21,533
You said you were starving
last night, didn't you?

133
00:15:36,090 --> 00:15:37,091
Let's go.

134
00:15:38,487 --> 00:15:39,488
Here.

135
00:15:41,073 --> 00:15:42,074
Enjoy.

136
00:15:57,427 --> 00:15:58,428
What do you think?

137
00:15:58,500 --> 00:15:59,730
I don't eat meat.

138
00:16:01,193 --> 00:16:02,194
But it's fine.

139
00:16:02,927 --> 00:16:04,850
This is made from flour so I can eat it.

140
00:16:07,287 --> 00:16:08,527
What about egg? Can you eat it?

141
00:16:09,973 --> 00:16:12,170
Sure, if we don't have to kill them.

142
00:16:13,007 --> 00:16:14,008
I see.

143
00:16:21,907 --> 00:16:22,908
Here.

144
00:16:24,507 --> 00:16:27,147
Eat up. You can't only eat bread.

145
00:16:31,347 --> 00:16:32,348
Let's eat.

146
00:16:32,447 --> 00:16:33,448
Go ahead.

147
00:16:34,513 --> 00:16:35,514
Hey! Wait!

148
00:16:36,527 --> 00:16:37,930
Wait.

149
00:16:42,130 --> 00:16:43,131
Hey!

150
00:16:44,090 --> 00:16:45,370
We need a fork and a knife.

151
00:16:47,847 --> 00:16:48,848
You need to put it down.

152
00:16:50,320 --> 00:16:51,321
Come on.

153
00:16:52,071 --> 00:16:53,072
Wipe your hands.

154
00:17:13,693 --> 00:17:14,694
Is it good?

155
00:17:26,667 --> 00:17:28,290
Are we going to look for my mom today?

156
00:17:30,140 --> 00:17:31,520
Sure, let's do it.

157
00:17:32,400 --> 00:17:34,667
But first, I need to go to my company.

158
00:17:36,160 --> 00:17:37,161
Company?

159
00:17:38,540 --> 00:17:40,210
My company is where I work.

160
00:17:40,933 --> 00:17:43,507
We need to go there first,
I have an appointment with someone.

161
00:17:44,413 --> 00:17:46,607
He will help us find your mother.

162
00:17:52,113 --> 00:17:55,567
Bro, your son caught
one of the Mudan people.

163
00:17:58,140 --> 00:17:59,587
Can you hear me?

164
00:18:02,770 --> 00:18:06,120
Are you happy that your dream,
and what we are trying to do

165
00:18:07,140 --> 00:18:08,647
will finally come true?

166
00:18:44,893 --> 00:18:45,894
Hey, Mudan.

167
00:18:46,500 --> 00:18:47,501
Are you okay?

168
00:18:48,660 --> 00:18:49,661
I guess.

169
00:18:50,940 --> 00:18:52,450
I feel a little bit queasy.

170
00:18:54,600 --> 00:18:55,601
You will get used to it.

171
00:19:01,153 --> 00:19:02,154
Hey,

172
00:19:02,693 --> 00:19:05,260
do they need to wear
this to work every day?

173
00:19:05,694 --> 00:19:06,695
Yeah.

174
00:19:09,233 --> 00:19:10,780
This is Kusuma Company,

175
00:19:11,500 --> 00:19:13,650
a legendary Thai perfume company.

176
00:19:16,827 --> 00:19:17,828
I've never heard of it.

177
00:19:20,207 --> 00:19:21,208
You will.

178
00:19:23,980 --> 00:19:24,981
Let me see.

179
00:19:36,333 --> 00:19:39,050
Actually, you look cute
when you wear my suit.

180
00:19:47,680 --> 00:19:48,681
Good morning, sir.

181
00:20:05,700 --> 00:20:06,701
This is my office.

182
00:20:27,573 --> 00:20:28,890
People here smell so nice.

183
00:20:30,153 --> 00:20:31,250
Their scents are unique.

184
00:20:32,427 --> 00:20:33,428
What do you mean by that?

185
00:20:36,733 --> 00:20:37,734
Jasmine.

186
00:20:40,387 --> 00:20:41,388
Rose.

187
00:20:45,400 --> 00:20:46,490
Pine.

188
00:20:51,593 --> 00:20:52,594
You have a keen nose?

189
00:20:54,500 --> 00:20:56,220
We Mudan people are familiar with scents.

190
00:20:56,926 --> 00:20:59,586
We can tell what the
scents are from just by a sniff.

191
00:21:01,413 --> 00:21:02,414
Are you bragging?

192
00:21:05,333 --> 00:21:07,650
Hello, Mr. Vice President.
You're here so early.

193
00:21:10,893 --> 00:21:13,010
Hey, how do I greet him
properly in the Mudan way?

194
00:21:14,593 --> 00:21:15,594
I have no idea either.

195
00:21:19,987 --> 00:21:21,433
Good morning, Gaysorn.

196
00:21:22,220 --> 00:21:23,221
Morning.

197
00:21:24,473 --> 00:21:26,620
To prove that you weren't
just bragging to me earlier,

198
00:21:27,620 --> 00:21:29,250
can you tell me his scent?

199
00:21:30,947 --> 00:21:31,948
What is going on?

200
00:21:33,700 --> 00:21:34,701
I think…

201
00:21:36,260 --> 00:21:37,261
It is…

202
00:21:38,687 --> 00:21:39,688
Sandalwood.

203
00:21:43,867 --> 00:21:44,868
That's right.

204
00:21:45,367 --> 00:21:46,680
He wore his sandalwood perfume.

205
00:21:49,600 --> 00:21:52,140
Come on, let's do something fun.

206
00:22:09,770 --> 00:22:11,450
Sun, hit it.

207
00:22:16,173 --> 00:22:17,174
Here.

208
00:22:18,047 --> 00:22:19,048
Orange.

209
00:22:21,850 --> 00:22:23,730
Wrong. It's bergamot.

210
00:22:24,440 --> 00:22:26,250
It's considered a citrus fruit.

211
00:22:27,187 --> 00:22:28,250
You picked the easy one.

212
00:22:28,873 --> 00:22:29,874
Let me do it.

213
00:22:40,827 --> 00:22:41,828
Here.

214
00:22:43,850 --> 00:22:44,850
What about this one?

215
00:22:49,770 --> 00:22:50,771
It's floral.

216
00:22:52,207 --> 00:22:53,208
Smells so nice.

217
00:22:54,047 --> 00:22:55,048
What type of flower?

218
00:22:57,987 --> 00:22:59,570
I have no idea.

219
00:23:02,167 --> 00:23:03,770
I don't know this type of flower.

220
00:23:04,753 --> 00:23:05,953
I have never seen it for sure.

221
00:23:08,313 --> 00:23:09,650
But judging from its scent,

222
00:23:10,930 --> 00:23:12,570
I think it must be small flower,

223
00:23:14,160 --> 00:23:15,161
and it is purple.

224
00:23:16,847 --> 00:23:17,848
What?

225
00:23:20,640 --> 00:23:22,370
- Hey!
- This is lavender.

226
00:23:24,907 --> 00:23:25,908
Look,

227
00:23:25,953 --> 00:23:28,730
the flower matches your description.

228
00:23:29,973 --> 00:23:31,250
You're so talented.

229
00:23:42,753 --> 00:23:43,754
Hello, Uncle?

230
00:23:49,100 --> 00:23:50,101
Is everything okay?

231
00:23:51,153 --> 00:23:52,154
Wait a second.

232
00:23:53,970 --> 00:23:56,370
Something came up, can I
leave Gaysorn with you?

233
00:23:58,427 --> 00:24:00,490
Something just came up,
can you hang out with Sun?

234
00:24:04,433 --> 00:24:06,890
- You're incredible.
- I'm on my way.

235
00:24:07,307 --> 00:24:09,210
What about your Mudan guy?

236
00:24:09,850 --> 00:24:11,050
Didn't you bring him with you?

237
00:24:11,690 --> 00:24:12,691
Yeah, but …

238
00:24:13,053 --> 00:24:16,013
I didn't want to feed him too much
information. I don't want to scare him.

239
00:24:16,313 --> 00:24:19,314
We need to make it clear among us first.

240
00:24:19,780 --> 00:24:22,060
What is your plan to extract his scent?

241
00:24:22,327 --> 00:24:23,330
You can tell me.

242
00:24:25,300 --> 00:24:27,940
The first person who came up
with Bussaba scent knew how to do it.

243
00:24:28,380 --> 00:24:29,460
But he passed away already.

244
00:24:30,313 --> 00:24:31,314
What?

245
00:24:31,787 --> 00:24:33,090
He refused to tell us how.

246
00:24:33,500 --> 00:24:36,130
Your dad tried to imitate
similar scents instead.

247
00:24:36,667 --> 00:24:37,668
But he couldn't find it.

248
00:24:38,668 --> 00:24:40,850
That means nobody knows how to do it.

249
00:24:42,740 --> 00:24:43,930
What is our next move?

250
00:24:44,400 --> 00:24:46,060
We got the Mudan person already.

251
00:24:46,680 --> 00:24:49,480
I think we need to take
good care of him first

252
00:24:50,162 --> 00:24:53,200
and we need to observe
how he produces his scent.

253
00:24:53,970 --> 00:24:56,450
When we find out,
we can extract his scent.

254
00:24:58,621 --> 00:24:59,622
Sure.

255
00:25:00,273 --> 00:25:01,174
One more thing,

256
00:25:01,200 --> 00:25:04,573
I talked to your dad
that you got a person from Mudan.

257
00:25:05,650 --> 00:25:07,187
It seemed like he could hear it.

258
00:25:08,573 --> 00:25:09,813
He seemed so pleased this time.

259
00:25:10,807 --> 00:25:12,890
You need to try harder, okay?

260
00:25:21,547 --> 00:25:24,170
If we do nothing to these petals,

261
00:25:24,407 --> 00:25:25,730
their scents will vanish.

262
00:25:29,193 --> 00:25:31,850
But if we wish to preserve their scents,

263
00:25:37,440 --> 00:25:38,913
we need to use heat.

264
00:25:41,240 --> 00:25:42,245
When water is boiling,

265
00:25:42,660 --> 00:25:44,800
its vapor will bring the scent

266
00:25:45,013 --> 00:25:46,214
to move along this tube.

267
00:25:49,327 --> 00:25:51,767
The vapor will consense into droplets
at the end of the tube.

268
00:25:52,893 --> 00:25:54,370
You will see its seperation.

269
00:25:54,713 --> 00:25:57,810
Then we can extract intense essential oil.

270
00:26:09,873 --> 00:26:11,450
We use the essential oil

271
00:26:11,800 --> 00:26:12,801
to make perfume.

272
00:26:23,283 --> 00:26:24,803
Why do we need to do it
in such a complicated way?

273
00:26:26,673 --> 00:26:28,450
Why don't we smell real flowers?

274
00:26:29,530 --> 00:26:32,330
We don't have houses
in the mountains like you.

275
00:26:32,640 --> 00:26:34,207
And we are not surrounded by flowers.

276
00:26:34,953 --> 00:26:37,650
This is how to preserve flower's scents

277
00:26:37,747 --> 00:26:38,987
and send them around the world.

278
00:26:39,567 --> 00:26:40,568
But this method

279
00:26:41,347 --> 00:26:43,447
is like sucking out
the soul of the flowers.

280
00:26:50,960 --> 00:26:53,961
This is to preserve their
souls as long as possible.

281
00:26:54,773 --> 00:26:56,250
We don't let souls die easily.

282
00:26:59,513 --> 00:27:01,353
Why didn't you tell me
that you took him here?

283
00:27:06,013 --> 00:27:07,090
I'm done with my errands,

284
00:27:07,967 --> 00:27:09,970
let's talk about finding your mother.

285
00:27:12,887 --> 00:27:13,888
Let's go.

286
00:27:28,506 --> 00:27:30,010
Preserve the flower's souls?

287
00:27:31,913 --> 00:27:33,310
I never thought about that.

288
00:27:49,253 --> 00:27:51,267
This is a picture of my mom.

289
00:27:51,787 --> 00:27:54,587
Do you know where she is originally from?

290
00:27:55,307 --> 00:27:57,910
Does she have any relatives anywhere?

291
00:27:58,633 --> 00:27:59,833
She was born in the mountains.

292
00:28:00,980 --> 00:28:02,490
Her only relative is Mata.

293
00:28:03,706 --> 00:28:05,639
And Mata doesn't know where she is.

294
00:28:07,300 --> 00:28:08,301
What about your father?

295
00:28:09,600 --> 00:28:12,080
The only thing I know about him was
that he was from the city.

296
00:28:13,640 --> 00:28:15,490
My mom said that she
would take me to see him.

297
00:28:16,807 --> 00:28:19,730
She told me to wait and she never returned.

298
00:28:20,701 --> 00:28:22,963
Do you have other documents

299
00:28:23,327 --> 00:28:26,388
like a birth certificate
with you right now?

300
00:28:27,273 --> 00:28:28,553
I was also born in the mountain.

301
00:28:29,547 --> 00:28:30,947
I don't have any birth certificate.

302
00:28:31,193 --> 00:28:33,494
I don't have anything.

303
00:28:46,100 --> 00:28:47,101
Mr. Scent,

304
00:28:47,207 --> 00:28:50,450
we got very little
information about his mom.

305
00:28:51,022 --> 00:28:52,740
But I will try my best.

306
00:28:53,200 --> 00:28:54,287
Please take care of it,

307
00:28:55,740 --> 00:28:58,370
but no hurry.

308
00:28:58,780 --> 00:28:59,781
Why's that?

309
00:29:00,987 --> 00:29:02,610
I want him to meet his mom,

310
00:29:03,770 --> 00:29:04,930
but not so soon.

311
00:29:06,020 --> 00:29:09,170
I think it should take 2-3 months.

312
00:29:11,490 --> 00:29:12,491
I hope you understand.

313
00:29:12,993 --> 00:29:13,994
I got it.

314
00:29:14,060 --> 00:29:15,370
Don't worry about that,

315
00:29:15,503 --> 00:29:16,730
we still need more time.

316
00:29:17,713 --> 00:29:18,730
See you later.

317
00:29:37,520 --> 00:29:40,090
All done, we can go home now.

318
00:29:40,930 --> 00:29:42,050
I will drop you off at home.

319
00:29:43,627 --> 00:29:45,147
I don't want to go back to your place.

320
00:29:47,000 --> 00:29:48,170
Sure, your place is nice.

321
00:29:49,900 --> 00:29:50,901
But it feels lifeless.

322
00:29:52,750 --> 00:29:53,751
I feel trapped.

323
00:29:56,387 --> 00:29:57,388
Where do you want to go?

324
00:29:59,107 --> 00:30:00,310
Any woods around here?

325
00:30:01,010 --> 00:30:02,011
The woods?

326
00:30:27,760 --> 00:30:30,041
I'll take you to the small forest
on the rooftop instead.

327
00:30:38,847 --> 00:30:39,848
Living in the city

328
00:30:41,360 --> 00:30:42,890
is much busier than I imagined.

329
00:30:45,327 --> 00:30:46,490
It's like it never sleeps

330
00:30:47,987 --> 00:30:49,547
and there is always something going on.

331
00:30:50,727 --> 00:30:52,007
It's not as peaceful as my home.

332
00:31:00,473 --> 00:31:01,474
I'm quite used to it.

333
00:31:03,170 --> 00:31:04,571
Living in the city is not that bad

334
00:31:05,667 --> 00:31:07,107
it's just another type of lifestyle.

335
00:31:10,227 --> 00:31:11,228
It's fun.

336
00:31:13,090 --> 00:31:14,370
But it's quite shameful that

337
00:31:17,353 --> 00:31:18,353
there are no stars.

338
00:31:19,520 --> 00:31:20,930
Who said there are no stars?

339
00:31:51,200 --> 00:31:52,570
I brought the stars closer to you.

340
00:32:05,413 --> 00:32:06,414
Let's watch the moon.

341
00:32:47,933 --> 00:32:48,934
Hey!

342
00:32:55,147 --> 00:32:56,970
Is it exhausting working here?

343
00:32:59,587 --> 00:33:00,930
I saw you working all day

344
00:33:03,013 --> 00:33:04,170
and you got so stressed.

345
00:33:12,413 --> 00:33:13,693
There is so much pressure on me.

346
00:33:15,607 --> 00:33:17,290
I have succeeded my dad

347
00:33:19,690 --> 00:33:21,330
so I want everything to turn out well.

348
00:33:22,993 --> 00:33:24,730
I want to make him proud

349
00:33:27,593 --> 00:33:29,170
and I want my uncle to finally rest.

350
00:33:36,213 --> 00:33:38,250
Don't you want something for yourself?

351
00:33:48,333 --> 00:33:49,334
I don't know.

352
00:33:51,413 --> 00:33:52,414
I just feel like

353
00:33:54,113 --> 00:33:56,330
there are so many duties for me to fulfill.

354
00:34:00,360 --> 00:34:01,361
Hey,

355
00:34:02,647 --> 00:34:03,648
sometimes

356
00:34:05,987 --> 00:34:07,347
it's better to forget about others

357
00:34:10,333 --> 00:34:12,170
and do something for yourself.

358
00:34:25,210 --> 00:34:26,211
Hey,

359
00:34:27,340 --> 00:34:28,500
I want to tell you something.

360
00:34:29,593 --> 00:34:31,010
I never told anyone about this.

361
00:34:32,094 --> 00:34:33,095
What is it?

362
00:34:33,740 --> 00:34:34,741
When I was a kid,

363
00:34:35,613 --> 00:34:38,210
I stole my dad's perfume
and I sprayed it all.

364
00:34:39,367 --> 00:34:42,330
My dad whipped me so
bad and I was so smelly.

365
00:34:45,250 --> 00:34:46,330
You were so stubborn.

366
00:34:48,427 --> 00:34:49,428
You're right.

367
00:34:49,793 --> 00:34:50,850
When I was young,

368
00:34:52,450 --> 00:34:54,130
I climbed up a mango tree

369
00:34:55,207 --> 00:34:56,898
and there was a beehive on that tree.

370
00:34:57,613 --> 00:35:00,890
The bees attacked me
and my face was swollen.

371
00:35:01,833 --> 00:35:04,250
Also, the beehive dropped to the ground.

372
00:35:04,834 --> 00:35:06,251
And everyone came to get some.

373
00:35:06,687 --> 00:35:07,850
I didn't get anything.

374
00:35:08,666 --> 00:35:09,923
The bees stung your face?

375
00:35:10,330 --> 00:35:11,513
Yeah, all over my face.

376
00:35:11,840 --> 00:35:12,841
Where?

377
00:35:13,090 --> 00:35:14,770
- All over my face.
- Right here?

378
00:35:15,170 --> 00:35:16,410
- Yeah.
- Right here, too?

379
00:35:17,240 --> 00:35:18,241
Yup.

380
00:35:52,313 --> 00:35:53,314
Hey!

381
00:35:57,890 --> 00:35:58,891
You're hurt?

382
00:35:59,447 --> 00:36:00,448
Of course, it hurts.

383
00:36:02,320 --> 00:36:03,321
Whoa!

384
00:36:05,972 --> 00:36:07,212
Is this chair working properly?

385
00:36:11,360 --> 00:36:13,360
- Ouch!
- It's because you're heavy.

386
00:36:30,233 --> 00:36:31,393
You're not watching the moon?

387
00:36:36,050 --> 00:36:37,011
Of course, I still watch it.

388
00:36:37,047 --> 00:36:38,048
Just sit on the floor.

389
00:36:38,610 --> 00:36:39,611
What?

390
00:36:40,890 --> 00:36:42,310
My chair is broken.

391
00:36:42,650 --> 00:36:43,651
Then sit on the floor.

392
00:36:47,113 --> 00:36:48,114
Fine.

393
00:36:48,680 --> 00:36:49,681
Ouch!

394
00:37:09,907 --> 00:37:12,267
- Fire!
- Hey!

395
00:37:12,507 --> 00:37:13,850
What happened, Gaysorn?

396
00:37:14,000 --> 00:37:15,001
Move!

397
00:37:18,673 --> 00:37:20,770
Who told you to put foil in the microwave?

398
00:37:21,570 --> 00:37:22,571
You did.

399
00:37:23,210 --> 00:37:25,911
You told me to just put it in.

400
00:37:26,370 --> 00:37:27,410
Are you hungry?

401
00:37:28,887 --> 00:37:31,090
I am hungry, can I still eat it?

402
00:38:55,207 --> 00:38:56,208
Is it boring to you?

403
00:38:57,010 --> 00:38:59,110
I'm sorry, it took so long.

404
00:38:59,973 --> 00:39:02,111
Nope, I'm fine.

405
00:39:03,087 --> 00:39:04,687
I should be the one to apologize to you.

406
00:39:05,095 --> 00:39:06,410
I caused you some troubles.

407
00:39:09,690 --> 00:39:10,691
Don't say that.

408
00:39:12,796 --> 00:39:14,036
I brought you here

409
00:39:14,787 --> 00:39:15,987
so I need to take care of you,

410
00:39:16,530 --> 00:39:17,531
am I right?

411
00:39:21,710 --> 00:39:23,711
Are you hungry? Let's eat.

412
00:39:34,890 --> 00:39:35,891
Hello, Uncle?

413
00:39:39,160 --> 00:39:40,161
Yeah?

414
00:39:44,253 --> 00:39:45,253
Just a moment.

415
00:39:46,003 --> 00:39:47,163
I need to talk to my uncle.

416
00:39:52,773 --> 00:39:53,774
What's going on?

417
00:39:55,450 --> 00:39:58,710
Did you find out how the Mudan
guy releases his scent?

418
00:39:59,367 --> 00:40:01,210
- No idea.
- What?

419
00:40:02,853 --> 00:40:05,610
You're hanging out with him every day,
and you still can't find out?

420
00:40:06,850 --> 00:40:08,570
Are you just playing around?

421
00:40:08,980 --> 00:40:10,930
Your dad's condition can't wait any longer.

422
00:40:12,170 --> 00:40:14,730
I know and I am trying.

423
00:40:15,810 --> 00:40:17,490
I know what I am doing, okay?

424
00:40:24,187 --> 00:40:26,210
Mr. Scent, it is about Mr. Ray's event.

425
00:40:26,267 --> 00:40:28,810
The event will be held at 5:00 p.m. today.

426
00:40:46,290 --> 00:40:49,010
Are you free this evening?
Can you watch Gaysorn for me?

427
00:40:49,253 --> 00:40:50,253
I need to do something.

428
00:40:50,254 --> 00:40:53,290
I'm not free this evening,
I can't watch your guy for you.

429
00:40:55,560 --> 00:40:58,480
If you're so worried about him,
why don't you just skip your appointment?

430
00:41:01,370 --> 00:41:02,811
I would if I could.

431
00:41:03,690 --> 00:41:04,930
But this event is so important.

432
00:41:05,290 --> 00:41:07,010
What kind of event? Why is it so important?

433
00:41:08,093 --> 00:41:09,730
The launch of Ray's new product.

434
00:41:11,567 --> 00:41:13,568
I see.

435
00:41:14,353 --> 00:41:15,354
Ray, huh?

436
00:41:15,747 --> 00:41:17,273
What? What do you mean?

437
00:41:18,130 --> 00:41:19,330
Why is it so important to you?

438
00:41:20,250 --> 00:41:23,370
I can smell your old flame
on the verge of being reignited.

439
00:41:23,607 --> 00:41:25,290
Do you want to smell this?

440
00:41:28,130 --> 00:41:29,131
What should I do?

441
00:41:30,227 --> 00:41:32,010
If you don't want to leave Gaysorn alone,

442
00:41:34,570 --> 00:41:35,850
you should take him with you.

443
00:41:48,333 --> 00:41:49,853
Why didn't you get it done already?

444
00:41:55,760 --> 00:41:56,780
Where is Scent?

445
00:41:57,250 --> 00:41:58,810
I still can't reach him.

446
00:42:00,251 --> 00:42:01,610
What did Kusuma say?

447
00:42:02,530 --> 00:42:04,730
I still can't reach the company either.

448
00:42:05,633 --> 00:42:07,530
Nobody can reach him.

449
00:42:08,860 --> 00:42:09,861
Go!

450
00:42:22,413 --> 00:42:23,414
Congratulations.

451
00:42:28,300 --> 00:42:30,810
You're cranky again?
It's about Scent, right?

452
00:42:32,250 --> 00:42:33,251
No!

453
00:42:36,370 --> 00:42:38,730
This is not the first time
that he's made you feel this way.

454
00:42:41,330 --> 00:42:43,610
Why do you think I still
hang out with you, Mekin?

455
00:42:49,531 --> 00:42:50,532
I got flowers for you.

456
00:42:51,893 --> 00:42:53,320
So you should feel better.

457
00:42:56,890 --> 00:42:57,891
Fine.

458
00:43:01,793 --> 00:43:03,290
Come on, lighten up.

459
00:43:03,650 --> 00:43:06,170
It's your important day so smile. Come on.

460
00:43:14,490 --> 00:43:16,930
- Mr. Ray, can you smile for this camera?
- Sure.

461
00:43:19,920 --> 00:43:21,800
Look at this one, please.

462
00:43:22,427 --> 00:43:23,530
Emma is here.

463
00:43:23,633 --> 00:43:25,770
Wow! Emma!

464
00:43:25,860 --> 00:43:28,400
- This way, please.
- This way.

465
00:43:28,413 --> 00:43:31,490
- I want some pictures with both of you, so nice.
- Hello, darling.

466
00:43:32,027 --> 00:43:34,610
Smile this way, please.

467
00:43:36,330 --> 00:43:38,650
- Mr. Ray, can I interview you?
- Sure.

468
00:43:38,753 --> 00:43:41,170
Can you tell me more about the concept

469
00:43:41,180 --> 00:43:42,970
behind the collaboration with Emma?

470
00:43:43,010 --> 00:43:44,570
The concept of my product

471
00:43:44,680 --> 00:43:47,170
is to collab with the Kusuma brand

472
00:43:47,280 --> 00:43:50,650
to enhance premium quality
for Thailand and international levels.

473
00:43:51,010 --> 00:43:52,770
We invited Emma to join us.

474
00:43:52,847 --> 00:43:56,690
- Everyone knows Emma.
- Sure. She's so famous right now.

475
00:44:13,453 --> 00:44:15,730
- Mr. Scent is here.
- He is here.

476
00:44:17,890 --> 00:44:18,970
Can you look at the camera?

477
00:44:22,133 --> 00:44:23,770
Mr. Scent, look this way please.

478
00:44:24,427 --> 00:44:26,147
- Please look at the camera.
- This way too.

479
00:44:27,450 --> 00:44:28,610
It's fine.

480
00:44:30,920 --> 00:44:31,921
Hello.

481
00:44:32,690 --> 00:44:33,391
Good evening.

482
00:44:33,473 --> 00:44:34,474
Look here, please.

483
00:44:37,360 --> 00:44:39,450
Look here,
too. A little more to the left.

484
00:44:39,553 --> 00:44:40,554
Hello.

485
00:44:46,820 --> 00:44:47,980
There is plenty of food here.

486
00:44:48,690 --> 00:44:49,691
Are you hungry?

487
00:44:50,667 --> 00:44:51,668
Not really.

488
00:44:55,330 --> 00:44:57,810
This is a business type of party

489
00:44:58,121 --> 00:44:59,241
so it could be a bit boring.

490
00:44:59,847 --> 00:45:01,327
I will take you somewhere else after.

491
00:45:05,053 --> 00:45:07,770
Why did you bring flowers for?

492
00:45:10,933 --> 00:45:11,934
These flowers?

493
00:45:17,220 --> 00:45:18,221
Let's go.

494
00:45:18,580 --> 00:45:19,581
Excuse me.

495
00:45:21,987 --> 00:45:23,570
Mr. Ray, Mr. Scent is here.

496
00:45:25,850 --> 00:45:26,851
At last, you're here.

497
00:45:28,450 --> 00:45:30,050
Congratulations.

498
00:45:32,810 --> 00:45:33,811
Thanks.

499
00:45:38,507 --> 00:45:40,690
Who is he? Aren't you
going to introduce him to us?

500
00:45:41,170 --> 00:45:43,050
This is Gaysorn, he's my friend.

501
00:45:43,800 --> 00:45:44,801
Gaysorn.

502
00:45:45,840 --> 00:45:48,490
Mr. Scent, can we get a picture with you?

503
00:45:48,673 --> 00:45:49,770
Mr. Ray, you too.

504
00:45:51,047 --> 00:45:52,090
A little closer please.

505
00:45:53,490 --> 00:45:55,450
Alright, you can get a picture now.

506
00:45:55,520 --> 00:45:57,090
- Let's go.
- Welcome.

507
00:45:57,510 --> 00:45:59,370
- Look at this camera.
- Hey!

508
00:46:00,210 --> 00:46:01,811
- Hey!
- Look here too.

509
00:46:02,450 --> 00:46:04,710
- This one, too.
- Please smile.

510
00:46:04,770 --> 00:46:06,490
- Nice.
- Please look at this camera.

511
00:46:06,690 --> 00:46:08,291
- Thank you.
- Look this way, please.

512
00:46:37,160 --> 00:46:38,826
Who is the guy coming
here with your boyfriend?

513
00:46:38,850 --> 00:46:39,851
My ex-boyfriend.

514
00:46:45,773 --> 00:46:48,290
He seems like a nice guy,
not a stupid one like you told me.

515
00:46:49,170 --> 00:46:50,770
And he is taking a good care of his man.

516
00:46:51,807 --> 00:46:53,130
People can evolve.

517
00:46:55,540 --> 00:46:58,010
He learned his lesson because I dumped him.

518
00:46:59,241 --> 00:47:00,801
If he had been nice like this with you,

519
00:47:01,410 --> 00:47:03,050
you wouldn't have come to me, am I right?

520
00:47:24,020 --> 00:47:26,170
It's okay, I'll get you cleaned up.

521
00:47:28,813 --> 00:47:29,814
Excuse me.

522
00:47:35,113 --> 00:47:36,114
Where are you heading to?

523
00:47:38,020 --> 00:47:39,480
I see. To the bathroom?

524
00:47:40,021 --> 00:47:42,170
I'm about to go to the
bathroom. Let me take you.

525
00:47:43,010 --> 00:47:44,570
- It's okay.
- Hello, Scent.

526
00:47:45,340 --> 00:47:46,340
How are you?

527
00:47:47,210 --> 00:47:48,211
Let's go.

528
00:48:06,410 --> 00:48:07,411
What is your name?

529
00:48:09,407 --> 00:48:10,408
Gaysorn.

530
00:48:11,731 --> 00:48:14,130
I'm Ray. You've heard of me, right?

531
00:48:16,560 --> 00:48:17,561
No, never.

532
00:48:18,527 --> 00:48:19,528
Liar!

533
00:48:20,750 --> 00:48:21,850
Why would I lie to you?

534
00:48:23,700 --> 00:48:26,730
You really didn't know who Scent's ex is?

535
00:48:27,490 --> 00:48:28,570
What are you talking about?

536
00:48:29,290 --> 00:48:31,210
- I have no idea.
- Where are you going?

537
00:48:32,291 --> 00:48:33,292
Why are you so fidgety?

538
00:48:34,193 --> 00:48:35,194
I didn't do anything.

539
00:48:36,053 --> 00:48:37,055
Let me go.

540
00:48:38,560 --> 00:48:39,561
Hey! Let me go.

541
00:48:39,813 --> 00:48:41,250
Let me go.

542
00:48:52,373 --> 00:48:53,374
Help! Help!

543
00:48:53,650 --> 00:48:55,610
- Help!
- Gaysorn?

544
00:48:57,530 --> 00:48:58,531
Help! Help!

545
00:48:59,847 --> 00:49:00,848
Help! Help!

546
00:49:12,413 --> 00:49:13,493
You don't know how to swim?

547
00:49:19,410 --> 00:49:20,411
Gaysorn.

548
00:50:44,300 --> 00:50:47,600
I bought some fruit for you.

549
00:50:48,300 --> 00:50:52,600
Wait, it's just for me?
Why did you buy so much?

550
00:50:53,300 --> 00:50:56,799
Well, I brought you all the way
from the mountains.

551
00:50:56,800 --> 00:50:58,800
I won't let you go hungry.

552
00:51:00,335 --> 00:51:01,242
Sit, sit, sit.

553
00:51:04,500 --> 00:51:05,900
Looks delicious.

554
00:51:06,100 --> 00:51:07,600
Choose whichever one you want.

555
00:51:14,500 --> 00:51:17,000
Hmm... which one looks better?

556
00:51:18,800 --> 00:51:20,800
You can just eat both of them.

557
00:51:22,500 --> 00:51:24,000
One is enough.

558
00:51:25,800 --> 00:51:27,300
Which one looks more delicious?

559
00:51:34,300 --> 00:51:35,800
This one.

560
00:51:38,000 --> 00:51:41,000
This looks delicious.
Can I have a bite?

561
00:51:46,200 --> 00:51:47,200
Sure.

562
00:51:57,100 --> 00:51:58,100
Eat this!

563
00:52:01,800 --> 00:52:02,800
Is it delicious?

564
00:52:04,500 --> 00:52:05,500
It is!

565
00:52:19,000 --> 00:52:20,500
(Next Episode)
I'm sorry.

566
00:52:20,800 --> 00:52:23,300
From now on, I won't let anything
hurt you ever again.

567
00:52:23,800 --> 00:52:24,800
Trust me.

568
00:52:30,800 --> 00:52:33,500
If Gaysorn isn't back after a month,
I'm going down there.

569
00:52:33,700 --> 00:52:35,699
We need Gaysorn's sweat.

570
00:52:35,700 --> 00:52:36,799
The more, the better.

571
00:52:36,800 --> 00:52:38,300
Let's go for a run.

572
00:52:41,100 --> 00:52:43,100
Hey, let me wipe it for you.

573
00:52:50,000 --> 00:52:51,300
What are you doing?
